      "id": "FR_ENCHAÎNEMENT",
      "name": "enchaînement",
      "left_context": "[bdgvzʒ]$",
      "right_context": "^[aeiouɛɔɑãɛ̃ɔ̃œ̃]",
      "transform": "‿",
      "obligatory": true,
      "notes": "une amie → resyllabification"
    }
  ],
  "notes": "Standard Metropolitan French (Parisian). Nasal grapheme sequences (⟨an⟩, ⟨en⟩, etc.) only nasalise when NOT followed by a vowel or another ⟨n⟩/⟨m⟩; context rules needed for disambiguation. FINAL CONSONANTS: t, d, p, s, x, r typically silent word-finally in modern French. LIAISON: s→[z], d→[t], x→[z], n→[n] before vowel-initial words (sandhi). SOFTENING: c→[s] before e/i/y; g→[ʒ] before e/i/y. INTERVOCALIC s: [z] between vowels within a word. Sources: Léon (1992), Tranel (1987), Côté (2000).",
